ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. Have you felt ashamed of any of your personal habits?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 2. Have you worried about what other people think of any of your personal habits?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 3. Have you tried to cover up or conceal any of your personal habits?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 4. Have you felt ashamed of your manner with others?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 5. Have you worried about what other people think of your manner with others?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 6. Have you avoided people because of your manner?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 7. Have you felt ashamed of the sort of person you are?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 8. Have you worried about what other people think of the sort of person you are?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 9. Have you tried to conceal from others the sort of person you are?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 10. Have you felt ashamed of your ability to do things?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 11. Have you worried about what other people think of your ability to do things?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 12. Have you avoided people because of your inability to do things?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 13. Do you feel ashamed when you do something wrong?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 14. Have you worried about what other people think of you when you do something wrong?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 15. Have you tried to cover up or conceal things you felt ashamed of having done?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 16. Have you felt ashamed when you said something stupid?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 17. Have you worried about what other people think of you when you said something stupid?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 18. Have you avoided contact with anyone who knew you said something stupid?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 19. Have you felt ashamed when you failed in a competitive situation? Or Have you felt ashamed when you failed at something which was important to you?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 20. Have you worried about what other people think of you when you failed in a competitive situation? Or Have you worried about what other people think of you when you fail?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 21. Have you avoided people who have seen you fail?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 22. Have you felt ashamed of your body or any part of it?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 23. Have you worried about what other people think of your appearance?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 24. Have you avoided looking at yourself in the mirror?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: 25. Have you wanted to hide or conceal your body or any part of it?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little; 3= Moderately; 4= Very much

ElementDescription: ESS total score
Characterological score, i.e. shame about aspects of the self
Behavioral score,  (i.e.  shame  about  actions and behaviors)
Bodily shame score, i.e. shame about physical characteristics
